{
  "texts": [
    "The test results using the CoNLL2003 dataset showed the highest F-Score value of 93.32, compared to the OntoNote5.0 dataset of 89.44 and WNUT-17 of 49.72.",
    "The result seems influenced by the ratio between the size of the corpus and the number of entities.",
    "The OntoNotes5.0 dataset has more tokens and entity types but fewer entities than ConLL2003 and WNUT-17, as shown in Table 3.",
    "The WNUT-17 dataset comes from various sources: Twitter, comments on YouTube, Reddit, and Stackexchange.",
    "While OntoNotes 5.0 comes from the Linguistic Data Consortium [91]."
  ]
}